Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy describes the privacy policies and practices of PerBlue Entertainment, Inc. ("PerBlue") regarding its game,
Disney Heroes:Battle Mode
, and all associated or ancillary PerBlue services or platforms provided in conjunction with the game (collectively, "Game") however accessed and/or used, whether via personal computers, mobile devices, tablets, handheld devices, or through other interactive services, features, applications, and downloads.
We will refer to subscribers, customers, users, and others who download, access, use, purchase, play and/or subscribe to (collectively, "use" or "using") the Game as "Users" and "User", "You" or "Your" throughout this policy.
Most of our Users will use the Game as it was intended as a harmless way for friends and strangers to play together. Please take care with how you play the Game, and how you manage your information and communications on the Game.
Please be aware that any Personal Information that you voluntarily disclose on any public forum on the Game or through any action including but not limited to messaging within our Game, is publicly available and can be read, collected, or used by others, and could be used to send you unsolicited messages.
PerBlue is not responsible for any third party use of User profiles, personally identifiable information, or any other identifying information that you voluntarily choose to disclose publicly using the Game.
This Privacy Policy is incorporated into and is subject to the Terms of Use Agreement. Your use of the Game and any Personal Information you provide in using the Game is subject to the terms of this Privacy Policy and the Terms of Use Agreement.
1. Information PerBlue Collects
Users may need to provide all or some of the following in order to use the Game: Facebook ID, Game Center ID, Google Play Games ID, AndroidID/IDFV, GAID/IDFA, IP Address, and/or MAC Address to PerBlue to play the Game (collectively, "Personal Information").  All such Personal Information is collected by PerBlue solely to authenticate You, but all such Personal Information is stored in an encrypted fashion that cannot identify You. Your ability to use the Game is not contingent on your provision of any personally identifiable information to PerBlue.
If You connect to our third party customer support ticketing platform, we may collect Your e-mail and additional Personal Information to address Your support request, which may include connecting Your Personal Information to Your Game ID to resolve the support issue. PerBlue does not permanently connect this Personal Information to other information in the Game. PerBlue will only store this Personal Information for so long as is necessary to address Your support request. Other than this, PerBlue does not collect any other personally identifiable information and does not connect any information about Your use of the Game with any of Your Personal Information or any other personally identifiable information.
When You play our Game, we collect certain types of technical information that is not Personal Information about Your mobile device, computer, tablet, or any other method used to access and operate the Game ("Device"), including but not limited to device platform, type, carrier, default language, country, and time zone (collectively, "Device Information").
A User's Personal Information and Device Information will be retained for each User for as long as PerBlue’s business needs require as determined at PerBlue’s sole discretion, unless the User contacts PerBlue and requests to have his or her Personal Information and/or Device Information deleted in accordance with the procedure outlined in the section titled "How to Delete Information Obtained by PerBlue."
PerBlue may use data collected from You that does not identify you or contain any Personal Information, including any statistical information or information necessary to provide the Game to you.
Playing the Game may require the use of a device running Google Android or the Apple iOS.
2. Opt-In of Promotional Emails and Notifications
We do not currently send any promotional e-mail or notification.  If, at some point in the future, we decide to send offers, promotions, and/or information of interest, we will obtain your prior written consent. You can always change our mind and opt out of receiving such email.  To opt out of emails from us, please follow the unsubscribe instructions contained in the relevant emails or contact us at legal@perblue.com. Our applications may also deliver notifications to your phone. You can disable these notifications in your phone's settings or by deleting the relevant application.
3. Information PerBlue Collects from Visits
When Users and others visit our Websites, PerBlue collects the visitor's IP address (the unique set of numbers used to identify the visitor's computer), and his or her registered domain or home server. When Users use the Game, including the Game itself, Websites including the Forum and Support channels, or bug tracking system, PerBlue’s servers automatically record certain information about their usage from their mobile device and/or web browser. These server logs may include information web requests, IP address, browser type, browser language, referring / exit pages and URLs, platform type, number of clicks, domain names, landing pages, pages viewed and the order of those pages, the number of messages related to the User's profile, the amount of time spent on particular web pages, and the dates and times of requests.
If a visitor requests information by sending PerBlue an email, PerBlue may save the visitor's e-mail address and any other information that the visitor or User provides. This information will be used by PerBlue solely to provide services or products the visitor requests.
4. How to Obtain or Delete Information Obtained by PerBlue.
A User may have their Personal Information and Device Information deleted by contacting Game support. This will result in the Personal Information and/or Device Information being deleted.  A User may also obtain a copy of the Personal Information and Device Information collected and stored by PerBlue by contacting Game support.
