5. How Information Is Secured.
PerBlue uses a variety of physical, technical, and procedural safeguards to guard against loss, misuse, and alteration of Personal Information and Device Information. For example, all Personal Information transmitted from mobile devices to PerBlue is encrypted; access to Personal Information is limited to PerBlue and contractor personnel who need the information for providing the Game to players; and PerBlue uses and requires its contractors to use technical measures to guard against unauthorized access to Personal Information. PerBlue cannot, however, guarantee the security of any Personal Information, Device Information, or information collected from the Websites or other correspondence including e-mail. Despite PerBlue’s efforts to secure such information, it may be accessed, disclosed, altered, or destroyed by a breach of PerBlue’s physical, technical, and procedural safeguards. Users use the Game and visitors go to the Websites at their own risk. If PerBlue learns that a User's Personal Information, or Device Information has been disclosed to an unauthorized person, PerBlue will attempt to notify the User.
